Two-part cycle of seminars helping the students to prepare for graduating from the university - starting from the project/application for the final thesis or examination up to the defense process. The students will obtain practical skills for searching and using theoretical materials, for choosing and implementing measuring instruments and (self)analysis models, for interpreting data and linking it with theory, etc.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To support the process of students' bachelor thesis and examination compilation and defense.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1) knows how to compile a research project/examination application; 2) knows how to formulate research questions and examination goals; 3) knows how to choose and process empirical and theoretical materials in a correct manner (including knows how to refer to different sources); 4) knows how to choose and use measuring instruments and self-reflection models; 5) knows how to implement theoretical priorly obtained knowledge in planning and conducting the bachelor thesis and examination.
